questions.name: Recommendations

questions.name: Subjective Notes
questions.answer:

Owner reports much improved activity levels and overall demeanour.

questions.name: Dynamic Assessment
questions.answer: Mia looked sound and comfortable around the house.

questions.name: Palpation Findings
questions.answer: Reduced elbow flexion/extension (R>L), trigger points through latissimus dorsi and epaxial muscles. Hypertonicity through triceps long/lateral head. Increase muscle mass/tone on least affected limb.

questions.name: Treatment
questions.answer: Responded very well to manual and ultrasound therapy, despite initial nerves.

questions.name: Recommendations
questions.answer:
Forelimb protraction stretches to be completed 3 x per week when the muscles are warm.

Maintain her weight to avoid extra stress to joints.
